\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals to perennials; glabrous or with unbranched hairs, glaucous. Cauline leaves simple, entire, usually amplexicaul. Sepals not saccate; petals yellow, shortly clawed. Fruit an indehiscent 1(2) seeded silicula with a wide, often inflated, wing surrounding the loculus; loculus usually with a distinct longitudinal rib; stigma sessile .
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 A difficult genus requiring revision. Species {\b 4-8} are all very similar and some are probably better regarded as subspecies of {\b 7}.
