\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. I. allionii} P.W. Ball, {\i Feddes Repert.}{\b  69: }57 (1964) ({\i I. alpina} All. et auct. mult., non Vill.). Perennial with branched rhizome and vegetative shoots; flowering stems 10-30 cm. Cauline leaves with obtuse auricles. Petals (3-)4-5 mm. Silicula 15-25 × 8-13 mm, orbicular-elliptical, sometimes subcordate at the base.{\i  Calcareous rocks and screes. • S.W. Alps; C. Appennini.} Ga It.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. I. platyloba} Link ex Steudel,{\i  Nomencl. Bot. }{\b 1}: 440 (1821). Annual 30-100 cm. Basal leaves obovate-spathulate, obtuse; cauline leaves with acute auricles. Petals 2-2·5 mm. Silicula 8-10 mm, orbicular-elliptical, emarginate or obcordate.{\i  Granite cliffs. • W.C. Spain} ({\i near Perena}); {\i N.E. Portugal} ({\i Miranda do Douro}). Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. I. sabulosa} Steven ex Ledeb., {\i Fl. Ross.}{\b  1}: 212 (1841). Biennial 40-80 cm. Cauline leaves attenuate at the base, without auricles. Petals 4·5-6 mm. Silicula 17-30 × 4-9 mm, linear-oblong to oblanceolate.{\i  Sandy soils. N.W. shore of Caspian Sea}. Rs(E).
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. I. laevigata} Trautv.,{\i  Del. Sem. Horti Kiov.}{\b  1840}: 6 (1840). Biennial 50-100 cm. Cauline leaves with acute auricles. Petals 2-2·5 mm. Silicula 6-11 × 2·5-5 mm, elliptical, 2-3 times as long as wide, glabrous; central rib wide and thick.{\i  Steppes. S.E. Russia.} Rs(E). ({\i C. Asia})
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. I. costata} C.A. Meyer in Ledeb., {\i Fl. Altaica}{\b  3}: 204 (1831). Biennial up to 120 cm. Cauline leaves with acute auricles. Petals 2·5-3 mm. Silicula 9-14 × 3-5 mm, oblong-obovate, c. 3 times as long as wide, glabrous or pubescent; central rib wide, distinctly 3-ridged.{\i  Dry, stony places. S.E. Russia; Krym}. Rs(K, E).
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. I. praecox} Kit. ex Tratt.,{\i  Arch. Gewächsk. }{\b 1}: 40 (1812) (incl.{\i  I. lasiocarpa} Ledeb.). Biennial 50-100 cm. Cauline leaves with acute auricles. Petals 2·5-3 mm. Silicula 7-14 × 3-6 mm, obovate-elliptical, 2-3 times as long as wide, glabrous or pubescent; central rib slender.{\i  E., C. & S.E. Europe.} Bu Cz Hu It Ju Rm Rs(W, E).
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Plants intermediate between{\b  6} and{\b  7} are not infrequent.
\par

